Marine Corps Leadership fuses with Marketing. 20 plus years of highly successful leadership experience as a Marine Corps Officer and bringing that to bear in the ever-changing world of Marketing and Technology.

As Marines, we learn to adapt and overcome, I bring this mindset to your business to help you achieve victories in the boardroom and in the marketplace.

I use the Marine Corps 5 paragraph order process (SMEAC) to do this which consists of the following

✅ Situation – What is your problem that we need to solve
✅ Mission – What are your goals, vision, and destination for your business
✅ Execution – What are the strategic and tactical plans we need to implement for success 
✅ Administration & Logistics – What are the resources consisting of people, programs, and funding to support execution
✅ Command & Signal – Who are the key people that need to communicate and make decisions and take actions to move the plan forward

WHAT I OFFER FOR BUSINESSES:

❇️ Consulting – Using the Marine Corps Planning Process outlined above

I'm passionate about helping women organize their homes, businesses, and lives.

I've always been organized.  At the tender age of five, much to my parent’s dismay, I would show up at the neighbor’s doorstep with a dustpan and broom offering to clean. Throughout my childhood, I would constantly be organizing the closets, drawers, and cabinets in our house. 

It made perfect sense that I would end up in the field of accounting where I worked for thirteen years. I retired so that I could be home with our children and entered the world of direct sales. 

That is when everything changed! As my children grew, and my business flourished, I lost my parents within weeks of each other. Now my once-organized home and business were in chaos. Trying to manage a home, business and life became a struggle. Hours of research helped me get back on track and led me on the path to helping others get organized. I started The Sensible Organizer in 2006 to help others bring calm to their chaos and never looked back.

Os vídeos já publicados no site www.youtube.com/c/CarlosOtavioSchneider demonstram o toer do combate, visando inserir no mercado de trabalho todos os diplomados nas Instituições de Ensino Superior no Brasil e que sejam portadores de diplomas legalmente reconhecidos pelo Estado Brasileiro através do Ministério da Educação - MEC, direito este, usurpado pelo Parlamento Brasileiro, ao editar uma Lei inconstitucional e Ilegal, tendo em vista que o Estatuto da Advocacia foi elaborado pela Ordem dos Advogados do Brasil - OAB, tendo tramitado somente na CCJ da Câmara e na CCJ do Senado, sem que houvesse votação nas respectivas casas legislativas. Ademais, a sanção presidencial da Lei 8.906/1994 foi firmada por um presidente (Itamar Franco) que teve sua assinatura falsificada, o que torna o instituto imprestável para o direito Brasileiro, tudo comprovado por pareceres técnicos, atestado por peritos. Contudo vige no mundo do Direito de fato mas não de Direito. Por fim, o desrespeito a Lei 12.605/2012, que determina que as instituições de ensino superior expeça os diplomas dos formados, contendo a flexão de "Gênero" do formado ou da formada, a "Profissão" e o "Grau obtido". Contudo, desde o ano de 2012, a referida lei inserida no ordenamento jurídico, se tornou letra morta para o nosso país. Growing up in Brooklyn, NY, Chris Owens and his two brothers, Geoffrey and Mitty, could have been a folk or classical ensemble.  Each brother played a stringed instrument, percussion and sang.  But they also liked to rock ... and pop ... and funk.  So, Geoffrey learned guitar (but still plays viola) , Chris traded in the piano, clarinet and cello for an electronic keyboard (but still plays recorders), violinist Millard focused on percussion – and, to start with, they all embraced the Jackson 5 and The Beatles!

Chris has performed solo, with his own bands, and with other singer-songwriters and choruses.  Chris formed OBB - The Owens Brothers Band in 2014, following the deaths within three months of his father, Congressman Major Owens (D-Brooklyn, NY), South African President and freedom fighter Nelson Mandela, and the one and only Pete Seeger.  OBB made its debut during "SeegerFest" at several venues, including Lincoln Center’s Damrosch Park (NY). 

COVID-19 has now created a new world, for better or for worse.  Having lost his wife of 28 years to cancer in 2019, Chris decided that COVID needed to create new lives, not just terrorize and take lives.  Furthermore, now that the internet rules the arts, it was clear that there are too many performers named "Chris Owens”!

Thus, Chris Oledude has been born.  With the recording and release of "My Tower," Chris Oledude starts a new chapter in his life with an "old school" blend of blues, gospel, R&B, rock ... and Broadway.  "My Tower" is a catchy condemnation of COVID-19.

Throughout the years, Chris Oledude's music has blended original melodies and rhythms with hot solos, harmonies and topical lyrics to create powerful and memorable songs.
